### E-commerce Demo API Examples
### Make sure the application is running on http://localhost:8080

### Check current inventory
GET http://localhost:8080/api/inventory

###

### Get specific inventory item
GET http://localhost:8080/api/inventory/shirt-m

###

### Create a new order
POST http://localhost:8080/api/orders
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sku": "shirt-m",
  "quantity": 2,
  "price": 25.99
}

###

### Create another order
POST http://localhost:8080/api/orders
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sku": "shirt-xl",
  "quantity": 1,
  "price": 27.99
}

###

### List all orders
GET http://localhost:8080/api/orders

###

### Get specific order (replace with actual order ID from previous responses)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/orders/991adf2c-1d83-4ada-8c56-de766b30dca2

###

### Update an order (replace with actual order ID)
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/orders/991adf2c-1d83-4ada-8c56-de766b30dca2
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sku": "shirt-m",
  "quantity": 3,
  "price": 25.99
}

###

### Process a refund (replace with actual order ID)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/orders/991adf2c-1d83-4ada-8c56-de766b30dca2/refund
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sku": "shirt-m",
  "quantity": 2,
  "price": 25.99
}

###

### Create a replacement order (replace with actual order ID)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/orders/991adf2c-1d83-4ada-8c56-de766b30dca2/replace
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "originalSku": "shirt-m",
  "newSku": "shirt-xl",
  "quantity": 1,
  "originalPrice": 25.99,
  "newPrice": 27.99
}

###

### Cancel an order (replace with actual order ID)
DELETE http://localhost:8080/api/orders/991adf2c-1d83-4ada-8c56-de766b30dca2

###

### Add inventory
POST http://localhost:8080/api/inventory/shirt-l?quantity=5

###

### Remove inventory
DELETE http://localhost:8080/api/inventory/shirt-m?quantity=1

###

### Test validation - missing SKU (should return 400)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/orders
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sku": "",
  "quantity": 2,
  "price": 25.99
}

###

### Test validation - negative quantity (should return 400)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/orders
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sku": "shirt-m",
  "quantity": -1,
  "price": 25.99
}

###

### Test insufficient inventory (should return 409)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/orders
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sku": "shirt-l",
  "quantity": 10,
  "price": 25.99
}

###

### Test order not found (should return 404)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/orders/non-existent-order-id